OL,5, The new Archbishop of Wales has        
OL,6, apologised "unreservedly" for the      
OL,7, Church's handling of the retirement of 
OL,8, former Bishop of Monmouth Richard Pain.
OL,10,FBishop Pain stepped back from his      
OL,11,Fduties in July 2018 after concerns were
OL,12,Fraised by clergy and a church worker   
OL,13,Fabout his conduct. He later retired.   
OL,15,FTwo Church in Wales probes took place. 
OL,16,FOne examined disclosures under bullying
OL,17,Fand harassment policies.               
OL,19,FThe other looked at his drinking and   
OL,20,Fworkload.                              
